                <h3>Job Positions:</h3>
                <br>
                <div class="em_box"> 
                  <a name="productmanager"></a> <b>Position: Senior Product Manager</b><br>
                  <br>
                  Trellian looks for a multitalented Senior Product Manager to lead the design and development of the <a href="http://www.above.com">Above.com</a> Registrar. <br>
                  <br />
                  This is a hands-on leadership position to own the product strategy, development and execution and to work directly with the company principals. <br>
                  <br />
                  The ideal candidate must have a full understanding of the industry players with a strong pulse of the competitive environment.<br>
                  <br />
                  This is an excellent opportunity for the right candidate to demonstrate your proven leadership skills and have a direct impact to the bottom line. <br />
                  <br />
                  <strong>Job Responsibilities: </strong>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>Lead and run the overall Product Management </li>
                    <li>Define product features, functionality and product requirement</li>
                    <li>Provide competitive analysis, documentation and testing for new product/feature development</li>
                    <li>Manage status of new products/features development and implementation</li>
                    <li>Monitor system maintenance and proactively handle critical issues resulting from market changes </li>
                    <li>Act as the client advocate to assure Above meets their highest level of service and requirements </li>
                    <li>Identify third party partner opportunities to benefit new features/products </li>
                    <li>Represent third party integration requirements and needs</li>
                    <li>Collaborate effectively with management and technical support</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br />
                  <strong>Requirements: </strong>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>3+ years of product management </li>
                    <li>Exceptional ability to communicate verbally and in writing at all levels</li>
                    <li>Must be able to relate to and engage customer needs</li>
                    <li>Strong quantitative, analytical and technical skills</li>
                    <li>Ability to work in a fast pace, deadline driven results oriented environment with an entrepreneurial start up attitude</li>
                    <li>Maintain high degree of self-motivation and independent</li>
                    <li>Strong business ethics and work ethic a must</li>
                    <li>Bachelor's of Science Degree or equivalent experience required</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br>
                  Please <a href="/contact.htm?dept=employ">contact</a> us for more information. </div>
                <div class="em_box"> <a name="accountspecialist"></a> <b>Position: Account Specialist </b><br>
                  Location: Los Angeles <br>
                  <br>
                  We are currently looking for an Account Specialist who will contribute to the continued success of the Trellian Direct Search Network. <br>
                  <br />
                  The Account Specialist will work within a team environment and be responsible for account maintenances and account revenue growth. <br>
                  <br />
                  The ideal candidate must have online experience be organized, have good communication skills and be able to thrive in a fast pace and changing environment <br />
                  <br />
                  <strong>Responsibilities: </strong>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>Maintain and grow existing accounts by analyzing the client traffic for trends in behavior </li>
                    <li>Make adjustments and recommendation for problem solving </li>
                    <li>Optimize campaigns and grow revenues by expanding keyword suggesting </li>
                    <li>Identify new traffic in our network to grow revenues </li>
                    <li>Keep the team informed on changes, trends and opportunities </li>
                    <li>Generate ROI tracking and other required reports </li>
                  </ul>
                  <br />
                  <strong>Qualifications:</strong>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>Minimum of 1-year experience in Internet marketing, SEM, SEO, digital advertising or related experience </li>
                    <li> Knowledge of online advertising technologies and terminology </li>
                    <li>Strong interpersonal skills and experience collaborating in a team environment </li>
                    <li>Must be analytical, organized and detailed oriented with great attention to accuracy </li>
                    <li>Detailed oriented and analytical </li>
                    <li>Ability to multitask and meet deadlines </li>
                    <li>Self motivated and able to work independently as well as part of the team </li>
                    <li>Social Media Marketing a plus </li>
                    <li>BA/BS or equivalent experience </li>
                  </ul>
                  <br>
                  Please <a href="/contact.htm?dept=employ">contact</a> us for more information. </div>
                <div class="em_box"> <a name="programmer"></a><b>Position: PHP / Perl Programmer (AU, Melbourne, Beaumaris Based) </b><br>
                  <br>
                  Exciting full time role for an experienced PHP/Perl programmer to work on Trellian.com Internet Search Engine marketing tools such as:<br>
                  <br>
                  <a href="http://ci.trellian.com/">Competitive Intelligence</a>, <a href="http://www.keyworddiscovery.com/">Keyword Research</a> and others yet to be released.<br>
                  <br>
                  For this role the below programming languages and environments are:<br>
                  <br>
                  <b>Required:</b><br>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>PHP</li>
                    <li>Perl</li>
                    <li>PostgreSQL</li>
                    <li>OOPS experience</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br>
                  <b>Nearly as important:</b><br>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>Working knowledge of AJAX</li>
                    <li>ActiveX programming</li>
                    <li>Javascript Programming from scratch</li>
                    <li>HTML/XHTML</li>
                    <li>CSS</li>
                    <li>XML</li>
                    <li>Apache</li>
                    <li>Linux/Unix general experience</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br>
                  <b>Less required but handy:</b><br>
                  <ul class="pg_list">
                    <li>Oracle</li>
                    <li>MySQL</li>
                    <li>C/C++</li>
                  </ul>
                  <br>
